My meme

Garfield is both the inspiration for my life and for this meme, as the passage of time continues during uni I feel more and more connected to funny orange cat. I wanted to portray this through striking visual art and thus this masterpiece was born unto the world.

library(magick)
library(tidyverse)

# grab the images of garfield
garf1 <- image_read("https://i.pinimg.com/originals/7d/68/2b/7d682bceab5817cbf331cffa7abc674d.jpg") %>%
  image_resize("500x500!")

garf2 <- image_read("https://i.pinimg.com/736x/78/60/3c/78603c5a7003c63a2a479648859816f4--garfield-cat-garfield-comic.jpg") %>%
  image_resize("500x500!")

garf3 <- image_read("https://amlitmaroon.files.wordpress.com/2010/04/garfield1-718788-7084471.jpg") %>%
  image_resize("500x500!")


# Create the text panels that will go next to the garfield images
wk1_text <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                          height = 500, 
                          color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Uni Work\nIn Week 1",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

wk4_text <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                         height = 500, 
                         color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Uni Work\nIn Week 4",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

wk7_text <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                       height = 500, 
                       color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "Uni Work\n In Week 7",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 80,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")

# Combine all of the panels
first_row <- c(garf1, wk1_text) %>%
  image_append()

second_row <- c(garf2, wk4_text) %>%
  image_append()

third_row <- c(garf3, wk7_text) %>%
  image_append()

meme <- c(first_row, second_row, third_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE)

# Export the meme
meme %>% image_write("my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

When portraying the daily ritual of funny orange cat the static art form is not enough, he is far too active and far too funny and thus I had to think outside of the box and create a silent movie about funny orange cat. This is an original work as it combines both photography, text, and illustration to present a view into the world of funny orange cat.

library(magick)

# Frame of Text
frame1 <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                        height = 500, 
                        color = "#000000") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "A Day in The Life Of\nFunny Orange Cat",
                 color = "#FFFFFF",
                 size = 50,
                 font = "Impact",
                 gravity = "center")
# Image Frames
frame2 <- image_read("https://pbs.twimg.com/ext_tw_video_thumb/1535414263824670723/pu/img/btDVy7ZOmwqj3MPc.jpg")%>%

# Combine All Frames
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4, frame5, frame6, frame7)

# Create Animation
animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 1)

# Export Gif
animation %>% image_write("my_animation.gif")

print(animation)
